sql:
SELECT AVG(wind_speed) AS average_wind_speed
FROM cyclone_observations
WHERE cyclone_id = 1;

SELECT observation_time
FROM cyclone_observations
WHERE cyclone_id = 1;

SELECT name, max_wind_speed
FROM cyclones
ORDER BY max_wind_speed DESC;

SELECT name, max_wind_speed
FROM cyclones
ORDER BY max_wind_speed DESC;

external_knowledge:
cyclone properties refer to attributes of the cyclone such as name, start and end time, maximum wind speed, minimum pressure, category, basin, and origin; 
observations refer to recorded data about the cyclone at a specific point in time (e.g., observation time, wind speed, pressure, status); 
predictions refer to forecasted data about the cyclone at a specific point in time (e.g., prediction time, predicted wind speed, predicted pressure, predicted status); 
access logs refer to records of users accessing cyclone information (e.g., number of accesses, last access time, user's name, email); 
alert logs refer to notifications about cyclone-related events (e.g., number of alerts, last alert time, alert severity, alert status).

sql:
SELECT observation_id, MAX(wind_speed) AS max_wind_speed
FROM cyclone_observations
GROUP BY observation_id;

